nus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Rokeby was born in 1418, in Yorkshire, England, her father, Sir Thomas Rokeby, was 35 and her mother, Anne De Eure, was 25. She married John Wycliffe Esq. about 1436. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1454, in her hometown, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1418–1454":"1418–1454","1410–Male":"1410–Surnud","1412–Male":"1412–Surnud","1418–1480":"1418–1480","1418–Female":"1418–Surnud","1412–1444":"1412–1444","1436–1482":"10.jaanuar1436kuni9.jaanuar1437–1482","1436–1494":"10.jaanuar1436kuni9.jaanuar1437–1494","1383–1422":"1383–1422","1393–1421":"1393–1421","Aft 1421":"pärast 1421","1494":"1494","1383":"1383","1482":"1482","1393":"1393","1480":"1480","1436":"10. jaanuar 1436 kuni 9. jaanuar 1437","1412":"1412","1422":"1422","1400":"1400","1444":"1444","1454":"1454","1421":"1421","1410":"1410","about 1436":"umbes 1436","about 1444":"umbes 1444","1418":"1418","after 1422":"pärast 1422","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Wycliffe, Yorkshire, England":"Wycliffe, Yorkshire, England","Rokeby, Yorkshire, England":"Rokeby, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1418–1454":"1418–1454","1410–Male":"1410–Kuollut","1412–Male":"1412–Kuollut","1418–1480":"1418–1480","1418–Female":"1418–Kuollut","1412–1444":"1412–1444","1436–1482":"vuodesta10.tammikuuta1436vuoteen9.tammikuuta1437–1482","1436–1494":"vuodesta10.tammikuuta1436vuoteen9.tammikuuta1437–1494","1383–1422":"1383–1422","1393–1421":"1393–1421","Aft 1421":"1421 jälkeen","1494":"1494","1383":"1383","1482":"1482","1393":"1393","1480":"1480","1436":"vuodesta 10. tammikuuta 1436 vuoteen 9. tammikuuta 1437","